{"title_page": "Group 1 Automotive", "text_new": "{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Group 1 Automotive, Inc.\n| logo = Group 1 Automotive Official Logo.jpg\n| logo_alt = 2016 Company Logo\n| trade_name = Group 1 Automotive\n| foundation = 1997\n| founders = Bob Howard, Sterling McCall, Charles Smith, Kevin Whalen\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{nyse|GPI}}<br />[[S&P 600|S&P 600 Component]]\n| location = [[Houston]], [[Texas]]\n| num_locations = 283\n| area_served = [[United States]], [[United Kingdom]], [[Brazil]]\n| key_people = [[Earl J. Hesterberg]] (CEO)\n| services = Automotive sales, financing, service, repair and parts\n| industry = [[Car dealership]]\n| num_employees = 14,200\n| num_employees_year = 2017\n| subsid = Bohn Holdings, Chandlers Garage Holdings, GPI Ltd, Group 1 Automotive UK Limited, Group 1 Funding, Ira Automotive Group, Mike Smith Autoplaza, Mike Smith Autoplex, Miller Automotive Group, Miller Imports, Bob Howard Automotive East, Bob Howard Motors, Rockwall Automotive, Lubbock Motors, Maxwell Ford, Mike Smith Imports, Amarillo Motors-F\n| website = {{url|https://www.group1auto.com/}}<br>{{url|https://www.group1auto.co.uk/}}\n| footnotes = [https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1031203/000119312512052522/d264649dex211.htm www.sec.gov], [https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/gpi/profile/ finance.yahoo.com]\n}}\n\n'''Group 1 Automotive, Inc.''' is an international [[Fortune 500]] automotive retailer<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fortune.com/fortune500/group-1-automotive/|title=Group 1 Automotive|website=Fortune|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-25}}</ref> with [[Car dealership|automotive dealerships]] and [[Automobile repair shop#Auto body repair|collision centers]] in the United States, United Kingdom and Brazil. Group 1 sells new and used cars and light trucks, arranges [[Financial services#Insurance|financial services]], provides maintenance and repair services, and sells vehicle parts. As of 2019, the company employs over 15,000 people globally.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nThe company is led by former [[Ford Motor Company]] executives, CEO [[Earl J. Hesterberg]] and CFO John C. Rickel.<ref>{{cite web|title=Earl Hesterberg|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/earl-hesterberg/|website=Forbes|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/markets/stocks|title=Stocks|website=Bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nGroup 1 was founded as a public [[corporation]] in 1997 with B. B. Hollingsworth as Chairman and CEO. The founding dealership owners were Bob Howard of [[Oklahoma City]], Sterling McCall, Kevin Whalen of Houston, and Charles Smith of [[Beaumont, Texas|Beaumont]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://quotes.wsj.com/GPI/company-people|title=Group 1 Automotive Inc.|website=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://business.rice.edu/person/b-ben-hollingsworth|title=B. Ben Hollingsworth|date=2016-03-03|work=Jones Graduate School of Business at Rice University|access-date=2018-01-09|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chron.com/business/article/McCall-major-Houston-auto-dealer-dies-at-78-4876763.php|title=McCall, major Houston auto dealer, dies at 78|work=Houston Chronicle|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.annualreports.com/HostedData/AnnualReportArchive/g/NYSE_GPI_1997.pdf|title=Group 1 Automotive 1997 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=1997|website=www.annualreports.com}}</ref>\n\nSubsequent acquisitions in the US include the Gene Messer Automotive Group, Maxwell Auto Group, Ira Motor Group, Bohn Auto Group, Pat Peck Auto Group, and Miller Automotive Group. 2018 acquisitions included two dealerships in [[El Paso, Texas|El Paso]] and on 1 March 2018, 5 Mercedes-Benz and 3 Smart dealerships from Robinsons Motor Group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/article/group-1-automotive-acquires-a-couple-of-dealerships-in-texas-cm913064|title=Group 1 Automotive Acquires a Couple of Dealerships in Texas|date=2018-01-30|work=NASDAQ.com|access-date=2018-01-30|language=en-us}}</ref> These are based in Bury St Edmunds, Cambridge, Kings Lynn, Norwich, and Peterborough.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.am-online.com/news/acquisitions-and-deals/2018/03/01/group-1-acquires-robinson-s-mercedes-benz-dealerships-confirms-darren-guiver-as-uk-boss|title=Group 1 acquires Robinson's Mercedes-Benz dealerships, confirms Darren Guiver as UK boss|last=|first=|date=|work=AM-online|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nGroup 1 acquired UK dealers from 2010 to 2017, including: [[Barons Group]], Chandlers Group, Essex Audi Group, Elms Group, Think Ford, Spire Automotive, and the Beadles Group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordtoday.co.uk/news/business/business-news/elms-bmw-and-mini-dealership-in-bedford-sold-to-american-company-1-6449433|title=Elms BMW and MINI dealership in Bedford sold to American company|date=1 December 2014|website=Bedford Today|accessdate=16 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918071751/http://www.bedfordtoday.co.uk/news/business/business-news/elms-bmw-and-mini-dealership-in-bedford-sold-to-american-company-1-6449433|archive-date=18 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.am-online.com/news/dealer-news/2016/02/04/group-1-announces-acquisition-of-spire-automotive|title=Group 1 announces acquisition of Spire Automotive|website=www.am-online.com|access-date=2016-07-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.am-online.com/news/acquisitions-and-deals/2017/07/04/group-1-automotive-expands-jlr-and-gains-vw-through-major-acquisition|title=Group 1 Automotive expands JLR and gains VW through major acquisition|website=www.am-online.com|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.am-online.com/news/2010/3/1/group-1-automotive-acquires-barons-dealerships/21804/|title=Group 1 Automotive acquires Barons dealerships|website=www.am-online.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bmiresearch.com/articles/group-1-acquires-ford-dealerships-from-inchape|title=Group 1 Acquires Ford Dealerships From Inchape, Autos|date=2013-04-01|access-date=2018-01-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.basingstokegazette.co.uk/business/14906610.Think_Ford_create_30_new_jobs/|title=Think Ford create 30 new jobs|website=Basingstoke Gazette|language=en|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.am-online.com/news/2012/5/8/group-1-confirms-essex-audi-acquisition/30966/|title=Group 1 confirms Essex Audi acquisition|website=www.am-online.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n\nGroup 1 purchased Brazilian automotive firm UAB Motors Participacoes S.A in 2013, renaming the entity as Group 1 Automotive Brazil in 2015. Professional race car driver [[Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro (racing driver)|Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro]] and his family of dealerships were notable parts of this acquisition.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-group1automotive-aquisition/group-1-automotive-rolls-into-brazil-with-uab-motors-buy-idUSBRE90O04820130125|title=Group 1 Automotive rolls into Brazil with UAB Motors buy|date=2013-01-25|work=Reuters|accessdate=2018-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://andreribeirohonda.com.br/|title=Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro Honda Website|last=|first=|date=|website=Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro Honda Website|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAs of 2013, Group 1 became the third largest automotive retailer in the United States, and as of 2018, the company owns 163 dealerships in 15 states across the [[United States|US]], 18 in [[Brazil]], and 60 in the [[United Kingdom|UK]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonews.com/article/20141201/RETAIL07/141209973/group-1-snaps-up-3-more-dealerships-in-the-uk|title=Group 1 snaps up 3 more dealerships in the UK|date=1 December 2014|website=Automotive News|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://group1corp.com/company-profile|title=Investor Relations|website=Group 1 Automotive|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref> Group 1 also operates 31 collision centers in the US, Brazil, and the UK.\n\n==Locations==\nIn the US, Group 1 Automotive has dealerships in Alabama, California, Florida, Georgia, Kansas, Louisiana, Maryland, Massachusetts, Mississippi, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New Mexico, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas.  Their corporate headquarters is in the [[Memorial City, Houston|Memorial City]] district of [[Houston]], [[Texas]].<ref>\"[http://www.memorialcitydistrict.org/images/map_mcity_lg.gif map_mcity_lg.gif] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727080442/http://www.memorialcitydistrict.org/images/map_mcity_lg.gif |date=2011-07-27 }}.\" [[Memorial City]].  Retrieved on December 8, 2009.</ref><ref>\"[http://www.group1auto.com/contactfs.html Contact Us] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100510073742/http://www.group1auto.com/contactfs.html|date=2010-05-10}}.\" Group 1 Automotive. Retrieved on December 8, 2009.</ref>\n\n== Products and Services ==\nIn response to [[Used car|used vehicle]] retailing trends, the Val-U-Line brand was created in Q1 2018 to retail older vehicles with benefits like a 3-day/300 mile return policy and [[Carfax (company)|Carfax]] vehicle history reports.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Roberts |first1=Adrienne |title=Used-Car Sales Boom as New Cars Get Too Pricey for Many |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/used-car-sales-boom-as-new-cars-get-too-pricey-for-many-1537700401 |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref> Initial investment impacted forecasts but future earnings were positive, contributing to a 13.9% increase in used vehicle sales for 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Charniga |first1=Jackie |title=Group 1's launch of older used-car brand to eat into Q1 earnings |url=https://www.autonews.com/article/20180320/RETAIL/180329949/group-1-s-launch-of-older-used-car-brand-to-eat-into-q1-earnings |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Takahashi |first1=Paul |title=Group 1 Automotive: Used vehicle sales drive record profits in Q2 |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/article/Group-1-Automotive-Used-vehicle-sales-drive-13108829.php |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Takahashi |first1=Paul |title=Group 1 Auto sold more used cars than new cars last quarter for the first time in company history |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/article/Group-1-Auto-sold-more-used-cars-than-new-cars-13796246.php |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019 the company created AcceleRide, a [[Online shopping|digital retailing]] platform allowing customers to purchase a new or used vehicle online.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Szatkowski |first1=Danielle |title=Group 1 Automotive debuts online car-buying platform |url=https://www.autonews.com/dealers/group-1-automotive-debuts-online-car-buying-platform |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Takahashi |first1=Paul |title=Group 1 Auto expands online car buying platform |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/retail/article/Group-1-Auto-expands-online-car-buying-platform-13941224.php |accessdate=6 June 2019}}</ref> The platform also provides [[Car finance|vehicle financing]], [[Car dealerships in North America#Trading for cars|trade-in appraisals]], and offsite delivery options.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Palermo |first1=Nick |title=New Car Buyers Benefit from Home Delivery |url=https://www.autotrader.com/car-news/new-car-buyers-benefit-from-home-delivery-192052}}</ref>\n\n== Philanthropy ==\nWith individual dealerships engage in local philanthropic efforts often independent from the corporate office, Group 1 supports Houston-area causes focusing on community [[outreach]] and grade school education.  Employees regularly make brown bag lunches to support Kids' Meals and donated cargo vans for their [[Meals on Wheels]] deliveries.\n\nThe company partnered with SEARCH Homeless Services and [[Junior Achievement]] of South East Texas for events,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.click2houston.com/news/conroe-hs-senior-surprised-with-new-car-at-2017-junior-achievement-gala|title=Conroe HS senior surprised with new car at 2017 Junior...|last=Martinez|first=Jonathan|website=www.click2houston.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-19}}</ref> classroom mentoring and the JA Company Program in [[Spring Branch Independent School District|Spring Branch ISD]].  Starting in November 2017, Group 1 partnered with the [[Houston Independent School District]] to reward their [[Teacher]] of the Month recipients with a new vehicle to drive for the month.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blogs.houstonisd.org/hisdtv/2017/12/05/hisd-teacher-of-the-month-for-december-2017/|title=HISD Teacher of the Month for December 2017 \u2013 HISD-TV|website=blogs.houstonisd.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.click2houston.com/news/5-things-to-know-about-kazmere-dean-hisd-s-teacher-of-the-month|title=5 things to know about Kazmere Dean, HISD's Teacher of the Month|last=Aragon|first=Rose-Ann|website=www.click2houston.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://abc13.com/education/hisd-announces-first-teacher-of-the-month/2613478/|title=HISD announces first 'Teacher of the Month'|last=morning|first=tom koch, eyewitness news, anchor, morning news, eyewitness news this|date=2017-11-07|work=ABC13 Houston|access-date=2018-01-26|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== The Group 1 Foundation ===\nThe Group 1 Foundation was initially created to support employees impacted by [[Hurricane Katrina]], closely followed by [[Hurricane Rita]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/20-3412167|title=Group 1 Foundation Inc - GuideStar Profile|website=www.guidestar.org|language=en|access-date=2018-01-18}}</ref> This tax-exempt charity gives all proceeds to help fellow employees in times of hardship. Examples include supporting survivors of fatal car accidents and a fire at an employee's home.\n\nSubsequent natural disasters like the [[2013 Moore tornado]], [[Hurricane Sandy]], [[Hurricane Harvey]], and [[Hurricane Michael]] also marked the need for the Group 1 Foundation to assist their employees.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Companies|Texas}}\n* United States - [https://www.group1auto.com/ Group 1 Automotive]\n*United Kingdom - [https://www.group1auto.co.uk/ Group 1 Automotive UK]\n*Brazil - [https://group1auto.com.br/ Group 1 Automotive Brazil]\n\n[[Category:Auto dealerships of the United States]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Houston]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 1997]]\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1997]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Texas]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Advert|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Group 1 Automotive, Inc.\n| logo = Group 1 Automotive Official Logo.jpg\n| logo_alt = 2016 Company Logo\n| trade_name = Group 1 Automotive\n| foundation = 1997\n| founders = Bob Howard, Sterling McCall, Charles Smith, Kevin Whalen\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{nyse|GPI}}<br />[[S&P 600|S&P 600 Component]]\n| location = [[Houston]], [[Texas]]\n| num_locations = 283\n| area_served = [[United States]], [[United Kingdom]], [[Brazil]]\n| key_people = [[Earl J. Hesterberg]] (CEO)\n| services = Automotive sales, financing, service, repair and parts\n| industry = [[Car dealership]]\n| num_employees = 14,200\n| num_employees_year = 2017\n| subsid = Bohn Holdings, Chandlers Garage Holdings, GPI Ltd, Group 1 Automotive UK Limited, Group 1 Funding, Ira Automotive Group, Mike Smith Autoplaza, Mike Smith Autoplex, Miller Automotive Group, Miller Imports, Bob Howard Automotive East, Bob Howard Motors, Rockwall Automotive, Lubbock Motors, Maxwell Ford, Mike Smith Imports, Amarillo Motors-F\n| website = {{url|https://www.group1auto.com/}}<br>{{url|https://www.group1auto.co.uk/}}\n| footnotes = [https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1031203/000119312512052522/d264649dex211.htm www.sec.gov], [https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/gpi/profile/ finance.yahoo.com]\n}}\n\n'''Group 1 Automotive, Inc.''' is an international [[Fortune 500]] automotive retailer<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fortune.com/fortune500/group-1-automotive/|title=Group 1 Automotive|website=Fortune|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-25}}</ref> with [[Car dealership|automotive dealerships]] and [[Automobile repair shop#Auto body repair|collision centers]] in the United States, United Kingdom and Brazil. Group 1 sells new and used cars and light trucks, arranges [[Financial services#Insurance|financial services]], provides maintenance and repair services, and sells vehicle parts. As of 2019, the company employs over 15,000 people globally.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nThe company is led by former [[Ford Motor Company]] executives, CEO [[Earl J. Hesterberg]] and CFO John C. Rickel.<ref>{{cite web|title=Earl Hesterberg|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/earl-hesterberg/|website=Forbes|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/markets/stocks|title=Stocks|website=Bloomberg.com|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nGroup 1 was founded as a public [[corporation]] in 1997 with B. B. Hollingsworth as Chairman and CEO. The founding dealership owners were Bob Howard of [[Oklahoma City]], Sterling McCall, Kevin Whalen of Houston, and Charles Smith of [[Beaumont, Texas|Beaumont]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://quotes.wsj.com/GPI/company-people|title=Group 1 Automotive Inc.|website=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://business.rice.edu/person/b-ben-hollingsworth|title=B. Ben Hollingsworth|date=2016-03-03|work=Jones Graduate School of Business at Rice University|access-date=2018-01-09|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chron.com/business/article/McCall-major-Houston-auto-dealer-dies-at-78-4876763.php|title=McCall, major Houston auto dealer, dies at 78|work=Houston Chronicle|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.annualreports.com/HostedData/AnnualReportArchive/g/NYSE_GPI_1997.pdf|title=Group 1 Automotive 1997 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=1997|website=www.annualreports.com}}</ref>\n\nSubsequent acquisitions in the US include the Gene Messer Automotive Group, Maxwell Auto Group, Ira Motor Group, Bohn Auto Group, Pat Peck Auto Group, and Miller Automotive Group. 2018 acquisitions included two dealerships in [[El Paso, Texas|El Paso]] and on 1 March 2018, 5 Mercedes-Benz and 3 Smart dealerships from Robinsons Motor Group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/article/group-1-automotive-acquires-a-couple-of-dealerships-in-texas-cm913064|title=Group 1 Automotive Acquires a Couple of Dealerships in Texas|date=2018-01-30|work=NASDAQ.com|access-date=2018-01-30|language=en-us}}</ref> These are based in Bury St Edmunds, Cambridge, Kings Lynn, Norwich, and Peterborough.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.am-online.com/news/acquisitions-and-deals/2018/03/01/group-1-acquires-robinson-s-mercedes-benz-dealerships-confirms-darren-guiver-as-uk-boss|title=Group 1 acquires Robinson's Mercedes-Benz dealerships, confirms Darren Guiver as UK boss|last=|first=|date=|work=AM-online|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nGroup 1 acquired UK dealers from 2010 to 2017, including: [[Barons Group]], Chandlers Group, Essex Audi Group, Elms Group, Think Ford, Spire Automotive, and the Beadles Group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordtoday.co.uk/news/business/business-news/elms-bmw-and-mini-dealership-in-bedford-sold-to-american-company-1-6449433|title=Elms BMW and MINI dealership in Bedford sold to American company|date=1 December 2014|website=Bedford Today|accessdate=16 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918071751/http://www.bedfordtoday.co.uk/news/business/business-news/elms-bmw-and-mini-dealership-in-bedford-sold-to-american-company-1-6449433|archive-date=18 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.am-online.com/news/dealer-news/2016/02/04/group-1-announces-acquisition-of-spire-automotive|title=Group 1 announces acquisition of Spire Automotive|website=www.am-online.com|access-date=2016-07-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.am-online.com/news/acquisitions-and-deals/2017/07/04/group-1-automotive-expands-jlr-and-gains-vw-through-major-acquisition|title=Group 1 Automotive expands JLR and gains VW through major acquisition|website=www.am-online.com|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.am-online.com/news/2010/3/1/group-1-automotive-acquires-barons-dealerships/21804/|title=Group 1 Automotive acquires Barons dealerships|website=www.am-online.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bmiresearch.com/articles/group-1-acquires-ford-dealerships-from-inchape|title=Group 1 Acquires Ford Dealerships From Inchape, Autos|date=2013-04-01|access-date=2018-01-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.basingstokegazette.co.uk/business/14906610.Think_Ford_create_30_new_jobs/|title=Think Ford create 30 new jobs|website=Basingstoke Gazette|language=en|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.am-online.com/news/2012/5/8/group-1-confirms-essex-audi-acquisition/30966/|title=Group 1 confirms Essex Audi acquisition|website=www.am-online.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref>\n\nGroup 1 purchased Brazilian automotive firm UAB Motors Participacoes S.A in 2013, renaming the entity as Group 1 Automotive Brazil in 2015. Professional race car driver [[Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro (racing driver)|Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro]] and his family of dealerships were notable parts of this acquisition.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-group1automotive-aquisition/group-1-automotive-rolls-into-brazil-with-uab-motors-buy-idUSBRE90O04820130125|title=Group 1 Automotive rolls into Brazil with UAB Motors buy|date=2013-01-25|work=Reuters|accessdate=2018-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://andreribeirohonda.com.br/|title=Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro Honda Website|last=|first=|date=|website=Andr\u00e9 Ribeiro Honda Website|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAs of 2013, Group 1 became the third largest automotive retailer in the United States, and as of 2018, the company owns 163 dealerships in 15 states across the [[United States|US]], 18 in [[Brazil]], and 60 in the [[United Kingdom|UK]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonews.com/article/20141201/RETAIL07/141209973/group-1-snaps-up-3-more-dealerships-in-the-uk|title=Group 1 snaps up 3 more dealerships in the UK|date=1 December 2014|website=Automotive News|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://group1corp.com/company-profile|title=Investor Relations|website=Group 1 Automotive|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref> Group 1 also operates 31 collision centers in the US, Brazil, and the UK.\n\n==Locations==\nIn the US, Group 1 Automotive has dealerships in Alabama, California, Florida, Georgia, Kansas, Louisiana, Maryland, Massachusetts, Mississippi, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New Mexico, Oklahoma, South Carolina, and Texas.  Their corporate headquarters is in the [[Memorial City, Houston|Memorial City]] district of [[Houston]], [[Texas]].<ref>\"[http://www.memorialcitydistrict.org/images/map_mcity_lg.gif map_mcity_lg.gif] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727080442/http://www.memorialcitydistrict.org/images/map_mcity_lg.gif |date=2011-07-27 }}.\" [[Memorial City]].  Retrieved on December 8, 2009.</ref><ref>\"[http://www.group1auto.com/contactfs.html Contact Us] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100510073742/http://www.group1auto.com/contactfs.html|date=2010-05-10}}.\" Group 1 Automotive. Retrieved on December 8, 2009.</ref>\n\n== Products and Services ==\nIn response to [[Used car|used vehicle]] retailing trends, the Val-U-Line brand was created in Q1 2018 to retail older vehicles with benefits like a 3-day/300 mile return policy and [[Carfax (company)|Carfax]] vehicle history reports.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Roberts |first1=Adrienne |title=Used-Car Sales Boom as New Cars Get Too Pricey for Many |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/used-car-sales-boom-as-new-cars-get-too-pricey-for-many-1537700401 |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref> Initial investment impacted forecasts but future earnings were positive, contributing to a 13.9% increase in used vehicle sales for 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Charniga |first1=Jackie |title=Group 1's launch of older used-car brand to eat into Q1 earnings |url=https://www.autonews.com/article/20180320/RETAIL/180329949/group-1-s-launch-of-older-used-car-brand-to-eat-into-q1-earnings |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Takahashi |first1=Paul |title=Group 1 Automotive: Used vehicle sales drive record profits in Q2 |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/article/Group-1-Automotive-Used-vehicle-sales-drive-13108829.php |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Takahashi |first1=Paul |title=Group 1 Auto sold more used cars than new cars last quarter for the first time in company history |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/article/Group-1-Auto-sold-more-used-cars-than-new-cars-13796246.php |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019 the company created AcceleRide, a [[Online shopping|digital retailing]] platform allowing customers to purchase a new or used vehicle online.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Szatkowski |first1=Danielle |title=Group 1 Automotive debuts online car-buying platform |url=https://www.autonews.com/dealers/group-1-automotive-debuts-online-car-buying-platform |accessdate=4 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Takahashi |first1=Paul |title=Group 1 Auto expands online car buying platform |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/retail/article/Group-1-Auto-expands-online-car-buying-platform-13941224.php |accessdate=6 June 2019}}</ref> The platform also provides [[Car finance|vehicle financing]], [[Car dealerships in North America#Trading for cars|trade-in appraisals]], and offsite delivery options.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Palermo |first1=Nick |title=New Car Buyers Benefit from Home Delivery |url=https://www.autotrader.com/car-news/new-car-buyers-benefit-from-home-delivery-192052}}</ref>\n\n== Philanthropy ==\nWith individual dealerships engage in local philanthropic efforts often independent from the corporate office, Group 1 supports Houston-area causes focusing on community [[outreach]] and grade school education.  Employees regularly make brown bag lunches to support Kids' Meals and donated cargo vans for their [[Meals on Wheels]] deliveries.\n\nThe company partnered with SEARCH Homeless Services and [[Junior Achievement]] of South East Texas for events,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.click2houston.com/news/conroe-hs-senior-surprised-with-new-car-at-2017-junior-achievement-gala|title=Conroe HS senior surprised with new car at 2017 Junior...|last=Martinez|first=Jonathan|website=www.click2houston.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-19}}</ref> classroom mentoring and the JA Company Program in [[Spring Branch Independent School District|Spring Branch ISD]].  Starting in November 2017, Group 1 partnered with the [[Houston Independent School District]] to reward their [[Teacher]] of the Month recipients with a new vehicle to drive for the month.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blogs.houstonisd.org/hisdtv/2017/12/05/hisd-teacher-of-the-month-for-december-2017/|title=HISD Teacher of the Month for December 2017 \u2013 HISD-TV|website=blogs.houstonisd.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.click2houston.com/news/5-things-to-know-about-kazmere-dean-hisd-s-teacher-of-the-month|title=5 things to know about Kazmere Dean, HISD's Teacher of the Month|last=Aragon|first=Rose-Ann|website=www.click2houston.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://abc13.com/education/hisd-announces-first-teacher-of-the-month/2613478/|title=HISD announces first 'Teacher of the Month'|last=morning|first=tom koch, eyewitness news, anchor, morning news, eyewitness news this|date=2017-11-07|work=ABC13 Houston|access-date=2018-01-26|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== The Group 1 Foundation ===\nThe Group 1 Foundation was initially created to support employees impacted by [[Hurricane Katrina]], closely followed by [[Hurricane Rita]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/20-3412167|title=Group 1 Foundation Inc - GuideStar Profile|website=www.guidestar.org|language=en|access-date=2018-01-18}}</ref> This tax-exempt charity gives all proceeds to help fellow employees in times of hardship. Examples include supporting survivors of fatal car accidents and a fire at an employee's home.\n\nSubsequent natural disasters like the [[2013 Moore tornado]], [[Hurricane Sandy]], [[Hurricane Harvey]], and [[Hurricane Michael]] also marked the need for the Group 1 Foundation to assist their employees.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Companies|Texas}}\n* United States - [https://www.group1auto.com/ Group 1 Automotive]\n*United Kingdom - [https://www.group1auto.co.uk/ Group 1 Automotive UK]\n*Brazil - [https://group1auto.com.br/ Group 1 Automotive Brazil]\n\n[[Category:Auto dealerships of the United States]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Houston]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 1997]]\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1997]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Texas]]\n", "name_user": "Jminot92", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_1_Automotive"}
{"title_page": "NA-140 (Kasur-IV)", "text_new": "{{Infobox constituency\n|type=\n|name=NA-140 (Kasur-IV)\n|year=2018\n|abolished=\n|parl_name=[[National Assembly of Pakistan]]\n|member=[[Sardar Talib Hassan Nakai]]\n|image=Pakistan - Punjab - Kasur.svg\n|map1=\n|map2=\n|map3=\n|region=[[Kasur District]]\n|elects_howmany=\n|electorate=477,211\n|previous=NA-141 (Kasur-IV)<br/>NA-142 (Kasur-V)\n|next=\n}}\n\n'''NA-140 (Kasur-IV)''' ({{lang-ur|\u0627\u06cc\u0646 \u0627\u06d2-\u06f1\u0664\u0660\u060c \u0642\u0635\u0648\u0631-\u0664}}) is a constituency for the [[National Assembly of Pakistan|National Assembly]] of [[Pakistan]]. The constituency was created in 2018.\n\n==Area==\nThe constituency mainly consists of [[Pattoki Tehsil]] and includes areas of the Tehsil, inclusive of the city of [[Phool Nagar]], [[Balloki]], which were previously included in the now-abolished constituencies of NA-141 (Kasur-IV) and NA-142 (Kasur-V). Some areas of [[Pattoki Tehsil]], namely, Chak no. 34, [[Chakoki]], and [[Wan Adhen|Wan Adhan]], are included in the newly created [[NA-139 (Kasur-III)]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/delimitation2018finalissued/National%20Assembly.pdf|title=Final List of National Assembly Constituencies|publisher=Election Commission of Pakistan|year=2018|pages=39|access-date=2018-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180510050630/https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/delimitation2018finalissued/National%20Assembly.pdf|archive-date=2018-05-10|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Members of Parliament==\n===Since 2018: NA-140 (Kasur-IV)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Election!!Member!!Party\n|-\n|style=\"background-color: {{Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf/meta/color}}\" |\n|| [[2018 Pakistani general election|2018]] || [[Sardar Talib Hassan Nakai]]\n| [[Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf|PTI]]\n|}\n\n== Election 2018 ==\n{{further|Pakistani general election, 2018}}\nGeneral elections were held on 25 July 2018.\n{{Election box begin |title=[[2018 Pakistani general election|General election 2018]]: NA-140 (Kasur-IV)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ecp.gov.pk/ConstResult.aspx?Const_Id=NA-140&type=NA&Election_ID=10070&Election=GENERAL+ELECTION+25+JUL+2018|title=ECP - Election Commission of Pakistan|website=www.ecp.gov.pk|accessdate=16 September 2018}}</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link\n  |party      = Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf\n  |candidate  = [[Sardar Talib Hassan Nakai]]\n  |votes      = 124,644\n  |percentage = 44.19\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party=Pakistan Muslim League (N)|candidate=[[Rana Muhammad Hayat]]|votes=124,395|percentage=44.11|change=}}\n{{Election box candidate\n  |party      = Others\n  |candidate  = Others (ten candidates)\n  |votes      = 32,975\n  |percentage = 11.70\n  |change     = \n}}\n{{Election box turnout|votes=289,434|percentage=60.65|change=}}\n{{Election box total valid \n  |votes = 281,981\n  |percentage = 97.42\n  |change = \n}}\n{{Election box rejected \n  |votes = 7,453\n  |percentage = 2.58\n  |change = \n}}\n{{Election box majority|votes=249|percentage=0.08|change=}}\n{{Election box registered electors\n  |reg. electors = 477,211\n}}\n{{Election box new seat win\n  |winner = Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf\n  |swing = N/A\n }}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[NA-139 (Kasur-III)]]\n*[[NA-140 (Kasur-IV)]]\n*[[NA-141 (Okara-I)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:National Assembly Constituencies of Pakistan|Kasur]]\n\n\n{{Pakistan-constituency-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox constituency\n|type=\n|name=NA-140 (Kasur-IV)\n|year=2018\n|abolished=\n|parl_name=[[National Assembly of Pakistan]]\n|member=[[Sardar Talib Hassan Nakai]]\n|image=Pakistan - Punjab - Kasur.svg\n|map1=\n|map2=\n|map3=\n|region=[[Kasur District]]\n|elects_howmany=\n|electorate=477,211\n|previous=NA-141 (Kasur-IV)<br/>NA-142 (Kasur-V)\n|next=\n}}\n\n'''NA-140 (Kasur-IV)''' ({{lang-ur|\u0627\u06cc\u0646 \u0627\u06d2-\u06f1\u0664\u0660\u060c \u0642\u0635\u0648\u0631-\u0664}}) is a constituency for the [[National Assembly of Pakistan|National Assembly]] of [[Pakistan]]. The constituency was created in 2018.\n\n==Area==\nThe constituency mainly consists of [[Pattoki Tehsil]] and includes areas of the Tehsil, inclusive of the city of [[Phool Nagar]], [[Head Balloki]], which were previously included in the now-abolished constituencies of NA-141 (Kasur-IV) and NA-142 (Kasur-V). Some areas of [[Pattoki Tehsil]], namely, Chak no. 34, [[Chakoki]], and [[Wan Adhen|Wan Adhan]], are included in the newly created [[NA-139 (Kasur-III)]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/delimitation2018finalissued/National%20Assembly.pdf|title=Final List of National Assembly Constituencies|publisher=Election Commission of Pakistan|year=2018|pages=39|access-date=2018-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180510050630/https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/delimitation2018finalissued/National%20Assembly.pdf|archive-date=2018-05-10|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Members of Parliament==\n===Since 2018: NA-140 (Kasur-IV)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Election!!Member!!Party\n|-\n|style=\"background-color: {{Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf/meta/color}}\" |\n|| [[2018 Pakistani general election|2018]] || [[Sardar Talib Hassan Nakai]]\n| [[Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf|PTI]]\n|}\n\n== Election 2018 ==\n{{further|Pakistani general election, 2018}}\nGeneral elections were held on 25 July 2018.\n{{Election box begin |title=[[2018 Pakistani general election|General election 2018]]: NA-140 (Kasur-IV)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ecp.gov.pk/ConstResult.aspx?Const_Id=NA-140&type=NA&Election_ID=10070&Election=GENERAL+ELECTION+25+JUL+2018|title=ECP - Election Commission of Pakistan|website=www.ecp.gov.pk|accessdate=16 September 2018}}</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link\n  |party      = Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf\n  |candidate  = [[Sardar Talib Hassan Nakai]]\n  |votes      = 124,644\n  |percentage = 44.19\n  |c