{"title_page": "Maria Lamb", "text_new": "{{short description|American speed skater}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = Maria Lamb\n| image          = 2013 WSDC Sochi - Maria Lamb.JPG\n| image_size     =\n| caption        =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1986|1|4}}\n| birth_place    = [[St. Paul, Minnesota]]\n| country        = {{USA}}\n| sport          = [[Speed skating]]\n| headercolor    = lightsteelblue\n| show-medals    =\n| medaltemplates =\n}}\n\n'''Maria Lamb''' (born January 4, 1986, in [[St. Paul, Minnesota]]) is an Olympic [[speed skating|speed skater]] from [[River Falls, Wisconsin]], who competed in 1500 m and the team pursuit at the [[2006 Winter Olympics]]. She was also selected to compete in the 5000 m for the US at the [[2010 Winter Olympics|2010]] and [[2014 Winter Olympics]].\n\n{{PersonalRecordsTop|ref=<ref>{{cite web\n |url        = http://www.speedskatingresults.com/index.php?p=17&s=231\n |title      = Maria Lamb\n |last       = \n |first      = \n |date       = \n |work       = \n |publisher  = www.speedskatingresults.com\n |accessdate = May 13, 2014\n}}</ref>}}\n{{PersonalRecordsSport|Women's [[speed skating]]}}\n{{PersonalRecordsMiddle|500 m|39.29|December 27, 2005|[[Utah Olympic Oval]], Salt Lake City|}}\n{{PersonalRecordsMiddle|1000 m|1:17.34|December 31, 2005|Utah Olympic Oval, Salt Lake City|}}\n{{PersonalRecordsMiddle|1500 m|1:58.03|December 30, 2005|Utah Olympic Oval, Salt Lake City|}}\n{{PersonalRecordsMiddle|3000 m|4:08.90|November 18, 2005|Utah Olympic Oval, Salt Lake City|}}\n{{PersonalRecordsMiddle|5000 m|7:09.62|December 30, 2009|Utah Olympic Oval, Salt Lake City|}}\n{{PersonalRecordsMiddle|10000 m|16:02.01|March 21, 2003|[[Olympic Oval]], Calgary|}}\n{{PersonalRecordsBottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n* [http://www.usspeedskating.org/athlete/maria-lamb Maria Lamb] profile at USSpeedskating.org\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.usspeedskating.org/rosters/Lamb.html |title=Maria Lamb profile at USSpeedskatin