6/44th-guillermo-mendoza-box-office-entertainment-awards \"44th Guillermo Mendoza Box-Office Entertainment Awards\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403190603/http://www.pep.ph/photos/3796/44th-guillermo-mendoza-box-office-entertainment-awards |date=April 3, 2019 }}. ''Pep.ph''. Retrieved May 19, 2014.</ref>\n|-\n| [[41st International Emmy Awards]]\n| Best News Program\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/12412/gma-739s-24-oras-and-i-witness-nominees-in-this-year39s-international-emmy-awards |title=GMA-7's 24 Oras and I-Witness, nominees in this year's International Emmy Awards |date=August 18, 2013 |accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Northwest Samar State University Annual Awards\n| Best News and Public Affairs Program\n| {{won}}\n! rowspan=\"3\" |\n|-\n| Best News and Public Affairs Male Program Anchor\n| Mike Enriquez\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best News and Public Affairs Female Program Anchor\n| Mel Tiangco\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[27th PMPC Star Awards for Television]]\n| Best News Program\n| ''24 Oras''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lionheartv.net/2013/11/full-list-of-winners-of-the-27th-star-awards-for-television/ |title=Full list of winners of the 27th Star Awards for Television |accessdate=April 28, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Female Newscaster\n| Mel Tiangco\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Male Newscaster\n| Mike Enriquez\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| UPLB Isko't Iska's Broadcast Choice Awards\n| Best Field Reporter\n| [[Jiggy Manicad]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| US International Film and Video Festival\n| Certificate for Creative Excellence, Newscast category (Sendong tragedy)\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''24 Oras''\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2013/06/19/955578/gma-network-wins-2013-us-filmvideo-fest|title=GMA Network wins in 2013 US film/video fest|website=philstar.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2014\n| George Foster Peabody Awards\n| Best News Cov